  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of OBS Studio</title>

    <para>
      First apply a patch to allow EGL libraries from
      <application>Mesa</application>:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>patch -Np1 -i ../obs-studio-&obs-studio-version;-allow_mesa.patch</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Install <application>OBS Studio</application> by running the following
      commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>mkdir build &amp;&amp;
cd    build &amp;&amp;

cmake -D CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr             \
      -D CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release              \
      -D ENABLE_AJA=OFF                        \
      -D ENABLE_JACK=OFF                       \
      -D ENABLE_VLC=OFF                        \
      -D ENABLE_BROWSER=OFF                    \
      -D ENABLE_WEBRTC=OFF                     \
      -D ENABLE_WEBSOCKET=OFF                  \
      -D ENABLE_V4L2=OFF                       \
      -D ENABLE_NEW_MPEGTS_OUTPUT=OFF          \
      -D ENABLE_RNNOISE=OFF                    \
      -D ENABLE_NVENC=OFF                      \
      -D ENABLE_NVENC_FFMPEG_IDS=OFF           \
      -D ENABLE_QSV11=OFF                      \
      -D ENABLE_SCRIPTING=OFF                  \
      -D OBS_COMPILE_DEPRECATION_AS_WARNING=ON \
      -G Ninja -Wno-dev .. &amp;&amp;

ninja</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the &root; user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>ninja install</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

